"guidebook.chapter.Title.FAQ": "[center][font=dialogue]Frequently Asked Questions:[/font][/center]
 
[color=maroon]How do I advance the story?[/color]
This entire mod progresses linearly. See all of Mateo's events, meet {{TrueName}}. See all of {{TrueName}}'s events, meet Cirrus. See all of Cirrus' events, meet Roslin. See most of Roslin's events, meet Dandelion. See their remaining events, and proceed to the final dungeon and the associated final boss. By then, you will have unlocked most of everything. What remains will be documented here.
 
[color=maroon]Where are the fish?[/color]
Most fish added by S&S are in available in either the [color=green]Druid's Grove[/color] or the [color=green]Pocket Dimension[/color], and are not time restricted.
 
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_SalmonOfKnowledge][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:32,144,16,16] Salmon of Knowledge[/itemtooltip]: 
Available in Spring and Summer in any weather.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_Fastitocalon][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:48,144,16,16] Fastitocalon[/itemtooltip]: 
Always available in any season, any weather.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_PallidSailfin][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:64,144,16,16] Pallid Sailfin[/itemtooltip]: 
Available in Spring and Winter in Sunny weather.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_GiantDragonfish][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:80,144,16,16] Giant Dragonfish[/itemtooltip]: 
Available in Fall and Winter in Rainy weather.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_FiveLinedConstellationFish][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:96,144,16,16] Five Lined Constellation Fish[/itemtooltip]: 
Available in Summer and Fall in Sunny weather.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_GoldieTheBatteryPoweredFish][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:144,160,16,16] Goldie the Battery Powered Fish[/itemtooltip]: 
Always available in the [color=green]Druid Tower[/color].
 
[color=maroon]How do I get all of the food recipes?[/color]
Some are sent in the mail, some are part of ranking the Druidics Skill, most are given during events, and one is sold at the Lion's Mane after unlocking the Deep Dark.
 
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_Steak_on_a_Stake][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/VioletMoonFood:0,0,16,16] Stake on a Stake[/itemtooltip]: Mailed by Stiles.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_ScotchEgg][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/VioletMoonFood:16,0,16,16] Scotch Egg[/itemtooltip]: Mailed by Stiles.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_Hand_Pressed_Apple_Cider][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/VioletMoonFood:32,0,16,16] Hand-Pressed Apple Cider[/itemtooltip]: Mailed by Stiles.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_Fruit_Hand_Pie][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/VioletMoonFood:48,0,16,16] Fruit Hand Pie[/itemtooltip]: Mailed by Stiles.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_Smoked_TurkeyLeg][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/VioletMoonFood:64,0,16,16] Smoked Turkey Leg[/itemtooltip]: Mailed by Stiles.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_autumnalstew][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:128,16,16,16] Autumnal Stew[/itemtooltip]: Mailed by Mateo.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_salishbourbon][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:112,16,16,16] Salish Bourbon[/itemtooltip]: Mailed by Mateo.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_dandeliongreens][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:144,16,16,16] Dandelion Greens[/itemtooltip]: Mailed by Dandelion.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_mushroomsredsauce][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:112,32,16,16] Mushrooms and Red Sauce[/itemtooltip]: via Druidics.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_ferngreensandpineapple][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:128,32,16,16] Fern Greens and Pineapple[/itemtooltip]: via Druidics.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_ancienthuckleberryicecream][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:144,32,16,16] Ancient Huckleberry Ice Cream[/itemtooltip]: via Druidics.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_lavaeelandstirfriedancientbottlegourd][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:0,48,16,16] Lava Eel & Bottle Gourd[/itemtooltip]: via Druidics.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_portfiredrakesparkler][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:0,32,16,16] Portfire Drake Sparkler[/itemtooltip]: Given by Cirrus.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_zuzustylepizza][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:96,64,16,16] ZuZu Style Pizza[/itemtooltip]: Given by Cirrus.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_zuzustylebagelwithlox][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:112,64,16,16] ZuZu Style Bagel with Lox[/itemtooltip]: Given by Cirrus.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_zuzustylecheesecake][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:128,64,16,16] ZuZu Style Cheesecake[/itemtooltip]: Given by Cirrus.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_zuzustyleclamchowder][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:144,64,16,16] ZuZu Style Clam Chowder[/itemtooltip]: Given by Cirrus.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_ancientsweettea][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:64,128,16,16] Ancient Sweet Tea[/itemtooltip]: Given by Dandelion.
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_farafieldsnack][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:128,176,16,16] Farafield Snack[/itemtooltip]: The Lion's Mane.
 
[color=maroon]What are the Ginger Beer flavors?[/color]
You can craft Old-Fashioned Fermenters after learning how from Cirrus. Add ginger and fruit to make flavored Ginger Beer, which can be aged.
 
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_orangegingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:96,112,16,16] Orange Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_blueberrygingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:112,112,16,16] Blueberry Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_pineapplegingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:128,112,16,16] Pineapple Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_rhubarbgingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:144,112,16,16] Rhubarb Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_strawberrygingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:0,128,16,16] Strawberry Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_peachgingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:16,128,16,16] Peach Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_ancientfruitgingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:32,128,16,16] Ancient Fruit Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_ancienthuckleberrygingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:32,128,16,16] Ancient Huckleberry Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_ancientappleberrygingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:32,128,16,16] Ancient Appleberry Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
> [itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_ancientelderberrygingerbeer][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:32,128,16,16] Ancient Elderberry Flavored Ginger Beer[/itemtooltip]
 
[color=maroon]How do I get Mateo, {{TrueName}}, and Cirrus' hoodies?[/color]
Marry them. 
 
[color=maroon]How do I turn off the Adventure Bar?[/color]
Ctrl+U is the default hotkey. This can be changed in the SMAPI portion of the S&S config. 
 
[color=maroon]{{TrueName}}'s seasonal quests have disappeared![/color]
They were removed permanently in 2.1.0. You can now progress as intended without them.
 
[color=maroon]The plus doesn't match my recolor![/color] 
This menu is used by S&S but is added by Spacecore. S&S covers most major recolors, but in case you'd like to add one, it can be targeted: 
> spacechase0.SpaceCore/ExtraEquipmentIcon 
 
[color=maroon]Another UI element doesn't match my recolor![/color] 
If it's your recolor and you've made the assets for it, please let us know and we can include it. If you have a request, please reach out on Discord or in the Nexus comments.
 
[color=maroon]Is there a standalone Skills component?[/color]
No. If you are interested in mechanics-only mods, there are other alternatives. S&S is, first and foremost, a content expansion. 
 
[color=maroon]Is S&S compatible with multiple spouse mods?[/color]
Use at your own risk, and report associated issues to the respective authors - not the S&S team. S&S's romanceable NPCs are not designed to be polyamorous, and {{TrueName}} is monogamous by design due to mechanical reasons.
 
[color=maroon]Who is Stiles Siddell?[/color]
A character planned for Sword & Sorcery: Final Mix, a standalone remake of this mod.",
"guidebook.chapter.Title.Cheats": "Arsenal
sns_encrustweapon ItemID - Encrusts held weapon
sns_coatweapon ItemID  - Coats held weapon
sns_alloyweapon ItemID - Alloys held weapon
Aether
sns_setmaxaether # - Sets max Aether, use reset in place of # to return to default. Not permanent, recalculates next day.
sns_refillaether - Refills Aether bar
Menus
sns_transmute - Opens transmutation menu
sns_research - Opens witchcraft/alchemy research menu
sns_shieldmenu - Opens shield menu (idk how this thing works)
sns_alchemy - Opens Alchemy menu
sns_arsenal - Opens arsenal (Encrust/Coat/Alloy) menu
Skills
player_giveexp SkillID EXPAmount - Sets EXP for custom skills
ID List:
DestyNova.SwordAndSorcery.Rogue
DestyNova.SwordAndSorcery.Druidics
DestyNova.SwordAndSorcery.Bardics
DestyNova.SwordAndSorcery.Witchcraft
DestyNova.SwordAndSorcery.Paladin
Misc
sns_repairarmor - Restores armor points to max
sns_finishorders - Finishes active SnS special orders
sns_startfinalephase2 - Starts Phase 2 of Duskspire fight
sns_playsong SongID# - Plays specified song

Fantasia Alla Marcia - song_buff
Battlefield Overture - song_battle
Invigorating Encore - song_restoration
Enduring Melody - song_protection
Rogues' Humorsque - song_npcbuff
Scherzo D'Inganno - song_attack
Ballad of Chronomancy - song_time
Track of {{HorseName}} - song_horse
Druid's Lullaby - song_crop
A Walk In Adante - song_obelisk",
  "guidebook.chapter.NEA.Intro": "[center][font=dialogue]Chapter 1[/font][/center]
  [center][font=dialogue]Never Ending Adventure[/font][/center]
   
This first chapter of S&S introduces you to Mateo, a charming rogue with a sordid history. Unravel their connection to the Museum's missing contents, help them reconnect with the townsfolk, learn the Artificer skill, unlock the Underforge, the Arsenal system, and found a new branch of the Adventurer's Guild.",
  "guidebook.chapter.NEA.Mateo": "[nospacing]
[nextposition=0,10][center=300][font=dialogue]Mateo[/font][/center]
[offset=118,50][image=Characters/Mateo:0,0,16,32:4]
[offset=-118,144][center=300]Pronouns: They/Them[/center]
[offset=0,32][center=300]Birthday: Fall 25[/center]
[nextposition=322,16][image=Portraits/Mateo:0,0,64,64:4]
[nextposition=0,288]
[/nospacing]
Mateo is an experienced adventurer with a kind heart who grew up in Pelican Town. Not only are they a skilled Rogue, but they have an inclination for blacksmithing. A good leader and better friend who'll always have your back.",
"guidebook.chapter.NEA.Emeritus": "[nospacing]
[nextposition=0,10][center=300][font=dialogue]Emeritus[/font][/center]
[offset=90,50][image=Characters/MateoEmeritus:0,0,32,32:4]
[offset=-118,144][center=300]Pronouns: He/Him[/center]
[offset=0,32][center=300]Not Friendable[/center]
[nextposition=322,16][image=Portraits/MateoEmeritus:0,0,64,64:4]
[nextposition=0,288]
[/nospacing]
Emeritus is a jovial Pepper Rex who hatches with one goal: to protect East Scarp from the crab menace. He's the most loyal sidekick there is, and loves the occasional kiss on the forehead. He'll return it with bonus slobber!",
