"guidebook.chapter.TOP.ElementalEssences": "[center][font=dialogue]Elemental Essences[/font][/center]
 
Upon meeting with Roslin in first event of Chapter 4, the Elemental Essences of[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_EarthEssence][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:96,128,16,16][color=brown]Earth[/color][/itemtooltip],[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_AirEssence][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:112,128,16,16][color=cornflowerblue]Air[/color][/itemtooltip],[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_FireEssence][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:144,128,16,16][color=Red]Fire[/color][/itemtooltip] and[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_WaterEssence][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:128,128,16,16][color=blue]Water[/color][/itemtooltip] will begin dropping around you.
 
Essences are used in quests, learning spells & alchemical recipes and using the [texttooltip=Teleportation Circle:Allows you to set up warp between two in-game locations.
Usage documented in the Magical Grimoire after learning.][color=purple]Teleportation Circle[/color][/texttooltip].
 
Collection method:
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_EarthEssence][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:96,128,16,16][color=brown]Earth[/color][/itemtooltip] - Mining
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_AirEssence][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:112,128,16,16][color=cornflowerblue]Air[/color][/itemtooltip] - Defeating flying enemies
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_FireEssence][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:144,128,16,16][color=Red]Fire[/color][/itemtooltip] - Defeating volcano enemies
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_WaterEssence][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:128,128,16,16][color=blue]Water[/color][/itemtooltip] - Fishing
 
[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_druidicessence][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:80,0,16,16][color=Green]Druidic[/color][/itemtooltip],[itemtooltip=(O)768][icon=maps/springobjects:0,512,16,16][color=chocolate]Solar[/color][/itemtooltip] and [itemtooltip=(O)769][icon=maps/springobjects:16,512,16,16][color=purple]Void[/color][/itemtooltip] all count as elemental essences.",

"guidebook.chapter.TOP.AlchemyTransmutation": "[center][font=dialogue]Alchemy & Transmutation[/font][/center]
 
[font=dialogue]Alchemy[/font]
Upon unlocking Sorcery, you will also gain the ability to learn how to make alchemical potions via the Philosopher's Stone menu. Like spells, these recipes are learned by exchanging [link=TOP/ElementalEssences]Elemental Essences[/link] in via sorcery research in the Magical Grimoire.
 
All potions apply buffs that last for 11 minutes and 40 seconds.
 
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_verdantpotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:80,80,16,16][color=purple]Verdant[/color] - +5 Foraging
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_scarletpotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:96,80,16,16][color=purple]Scarlet[/color] - +5 Attack
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_heatherpotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:112,80,16,16][color=purple]Heather[/color] - +5 Speed
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_zydratepotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:128,80,16,16][color=purple]Zydrate[/color] - +3 Speed, Defense, Attack
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_pistachiopotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:144,80,16,16][color=purple]Pistachio[/color] - +5 Farming
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_dahliapotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:0,96,16,16][color=purple]Dahlia[/color] - +1 Farming, Fishing, Mining
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_slushiepotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:16,96,16,16][color=purple]Slushie[/color] - +10 Max Stamina
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_matrixpotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:32,96,16,16][color=purple]Matrix[/color] - +5 Mining, +3 Magnetism
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_mcdougalpotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:48,96,16,16][color=purple]McDougal[/color] - +5 Luck
>[itemtooltip=(O)DN.SnS_toirneachpotion][icon=Textures/DN.SnS/SnSObjects:64,96,16,16][color=purple]Toirneach[/color] - +4 Mining, +4 Defense
 
[font=dialogue]Transmutation[/font]
If you find yourself in need of a specific [link=TOP/ElementalEssences]Elemental Essence[/link], you can transmutate one essence into another from the Transmutation menu in your Magical Grimoire.
 
The conversation ratio for essences is 4:1 (Default), 2:1 ([link=TOP/SorcererProfessions]Hedge Witch[/link]) or 1:1 ([link=TOP/SorcererProfessions]Master Alchemist[/link]) and will pull from the first available essence in your inventory.",

